-- Gold Extends Decline in London to $1,176.97, the Lowest Price Since May 24
-- Nicholas Larkin
-- 2010-07-20T10:04:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/gold-extends-decline-in-london-to-1-176-97-the-lowest-price-since-may-24.html

          
          
             Gold for immediate delivery dropped
as much as 0.5 percent to $1,176.97 an ounce, the lowest price
since May 24.  
 The metal traded at $1,177.70 at 11:04 a.m. in London.  
          
          


  


        